# Network Map

## How the current layout works

The deck remains available locally at `${LAB_LOCAL_URL}`. The lab is split into four layers:

- `core`: deck, Gitea, and n8n
- `ai-llm`: Open WebUI and Ollama
- `ai-image`: InvokeAI, SwarmUI, Fooocus, and their paired local image-generation runtimes
- `workbench`: Postgres and code-server environments

Each layer publishes its HTTPS endpoints on `localhost` through a dedicated gateway. In addition, the `workbench` layer also exposes `Postgres` on a dedicated host TCP port.

## Public lab endpoints

- Local deck: `${LAB_LOCAL_URL}`
- Gitea: `${GITEA_URL}`
- n8n: `${N8N_URL}`
- Open WebUI: `${OPENWEBUI_URL}` only when the `ai-llm` layer is enabled
- Ollama: `${OLLAMA_URL}` only when the `ai-llm` layer is enabled
- InvokeAI: `${INVOKEAI_URL}` only when the `ai-image` layer is enabled
- SwarmUI: `${SWARMUI_URL}` only when the `ai-image` layer is enabled
- Fooocus: `${FOOOCUS_URL}` only when the `ai-image` layer is enabled
- Node workbench: `${NODE_DEV_URL}` only when the `workbench` layer is enabled
- Python workbench: `${PYTHON_DEV_URL}` only when the `workbench` layer is enabled
- AI workbench: `${AI_DEV_URL}` only when the `workbench` layer is enabled
- C++ workbench: `${CPP_DEV_URL}` only when the `workbench` layer is enabled
- Postgres host access: `localhost:${POSTGRES_DEV_HOST_PORT}` only when the `workbench` layer is enabled

## Localhost multi-port routing

- `8443`: local deck
- `8444`: Gitea
- `8445`: n8n
- `8446`: Open WebUI, layer `ai-llm`
- `8447`: Ollama, layer `ai-llm`
- `8448`: InvokeAI, layer `ai-image`
- `8449`: SwarmUI, layer `ai-image`
- `8450`: Node workbench, layer `workbench`
- `8451`: Python workbench, layer `workbench`
- `8452`: AI workbench, layer `workbench`
- `8453`: C++ workbench, layer `workbench`
- `8454`: Fooocus, layer `ai-image`
- `${POSTGRES_DEV_HOST_PORT}`: Postgres host access, layer `workbench`

No DNS setup and no `hosts` file edits are required: just use `https://localhost:<port>/`.

## Certificate

The gateway generates a self-signed SAN certificate that covers `localhost` and `127.0.0.1`. You can download it from `/assets/lab.crt`.

## Internal segmentation

- `apps-net`: Gitea, n8n, Open WebUI
- `ai-llm-net`: Ollama and Open WebUI
- `ai-image-net`: InvokeAI, SwarmUI, Fooocus, and the optional image-generation runtime
- `data-net`: infrastructure databases
- `workbench-net`: Postgres and optional code-server environments
- `workbench-host-net`: dedicated bridge for the host-side Postgres TCP bind
- `services-egress-net`: selective outbound internet access for core services without direct exposure
- `workbench-egress-net`: selective outbound internet access for development environments

The only containers exposed to the browser are the layer gateways.
